        <section xml:id="sec-Advancedlearningobjectives26">
          <title>Advanced learning objectives</title>

          <p>
            In addition to mastering the basic objectives, here are the tasks you should be able to perform after class, with practice:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>
                Explain how the derivative of an inverse function is related to the derivative of the original function.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <p>
                Use derivative rules for <m>\ln(x)</m>, <m>\arcsin(x)</m>, and <m>\arctan(x)</m>.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <p>
                Use the relationship between a function and its inverse to develop the inverse function’s derivative rule (in particular: be able to do this “from scratch” for <m>\ln(x)</m>, <m>\arcsin(x)</m>, and <m>\arctan(x)</m>).
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <p>
                Differentiate a function involving logarithmic functions, arcsine and arctangent functions, and for which the derivative involves a combination of chain, product and quotient rules.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>

        </section>

